{"award_age":54.0,"bio_image":"full\/ac85b045d1909896c4ace4805b0f8cac93e9aa44.jpg","category":"Physiology or Medicine","country":"Australia","date_of_birth":"1951-09-30T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":null,"gender":"male","image_urls":["http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/thumb\/f\/f1\/Marshall_2008.JPG\/220px-Marshall_2008.JPG"],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Barry_Marshall","mini_bio":"<p><b>Barry James Marshall<\/b>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Order_of_Australia\" title=\"Order of Australia\">AC<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fellow_of_the_Royal_Australasian_College_of_Physicians\" title=\"Fellow of the Royal Australasian College of Physicians\">FRACP<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fellow_of_the_Royal_Society\" title=\"Fellow of the Royal Society\" class=\"mw-redirect\">FRS<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fellow_of_the_Australian_Academy_of_Science\" title=\"Fellow of the Australian Academy of Science\" class=\"mw-redirect\">FAA<\/a>, DSc (born 30 September 1951) is an Australian physician, Nobel Prize laureate in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Physiology\" title=\"Physiology\">Physiology<\/a> or Medicine (the only laureate born in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Western_Australia\" title=\"Western Australia\">Western Australia<\/a>), and Professor of Clinical <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Microbiology\" title=\"Microbiology\">Microbiology<\/a> at the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/University_of_Western_Australia\" title=\"University of Western Australia\">University of Western Australia<\/a>. Marshall and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Robin_Warren\" title=\"Robin Warren\">Robin Warren<\/a> showed that the bacterium <i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Helicobacter_pylori\" title=\"Helicobacter pylori\">Helicobacter pylori<\/a><\/i> (<i>H. pylori<\/i>) is the cause of most <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Peptic_ulcer\" title=\"Peptic ulcer\">peptic ulcers<\/a>, reversing decades of medical doctrine holding that ulcers were caused by stress, spicy foods, and too much acid. This discovery has allowed for a breakthrough in understanding a causative link between <i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Helicobacter_pylori\" title=\"Helicobacter pylori\">Helicobacter pylori<\/a><\/i> infection and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Stomach_cancer\" title=\"Stomach cancer\">stomach cancer<\/a>.<\/p>","name":"Barry Marshall","place_of_birth":"Kalgoorlie, Western Australia","place_of_death":null,"text":"Barry Marshall , Physiology or Medicine, 2005","year":2005.0}